Durban - Friends of Winnie Madikizela Mandela held an impromptu night vigil in Durban last night following the news of her death.

The vigil was attended by around 20 or more people and was held next to the wall of the former Durban Central Prison next to the Inkosi Albert Luthuli Convention Centre.

The site was chosen for its symbolic importance as the prison incarcerated many activist during the apartheid era.

Among those who attended the vigil was former Transport Minister and President Jacob Zuma spokesperson Mac Maraj, Umkhonto Wesizwe spokesperson Carl Niehaus, Kiru Naidoo, Human settlement MEC Ravi Pillay and activist Sinthi Qono among others.















