Addressing the few people who gathered, Naidoo said, “This gathering has no official standing. All of you that are gathered here are friends of mam Winnie. As soon as we heard the news of her passing, This was a spontaneous reaction, people just came out here over the past hour or so to pay their respect to her.”

Maharaj said Winnie’s life was worth celebrating. “On the one hand she represented the nobility for human freedom  and on the other hand she displayed human frailties that show that we are all human.”















